title: For Sale:  Springfield EMP 9mm (1911 style)
location: Western Cumberland County, Fayetteville, North Carolina
postcontent:
I received this EMP 9mm for Christmas from my dad, who bought a larger 1911 in 9mm.  He preferred the longer 5" barrel of a full-size, and said I could try this and keep it if I liked it or sell it if I didn't like it.  It shoots great, and is really a high quality gun, but I, too, prefer the longer barrel of a full-size.  I don't plan to carry this gun, which is really what it's for, so I am selling it.

This is a very unique gun; Springfield Armory designed a 1911-style gun around a 9mm architecture.  It's not just a scaled-down 1911; it was designed as a 9mm from the ground-up.  That said, it has all of the ergonomics that 1911 fans know and love, like the ambidextrous thumb safety that allows carry in a cocked-and-locked fashion.  Magazine capacity is 9 rounds (plus one in the chamber).  The magazines are very high quality, made in Italy for Springfield by Mec-Gar.  Folks, this gun comes with THREE of those high quality Mec-Gar magazines.  Rounding out the gun's features, it's got a very classy look to it, with the cocobolo grips, stain stainless upper slide and blackened aluminum alloy frame.  Sights?  It's got you covered with Trijicon night sights front and rear, dovetailed into the slide.

6.5" in length, 5" in height, and weighing in at 26 oz, it would make an excellent carry gun for someone looking for a very high quality and reliable 9mm in the 1911 style.

This gun shows very well, and is flawless in every way I can tell.  My dad bought it last spring, and together, we have shot no more than a few hundred rounds through it.  As pictured, it comes as you'd find it new in a gun shop, with the manual, case, magazine clip for your belt, and a belt holster.  This retails new for at or around $1,400.  Looking to get $950, and I'm pretty firm on the price, given the condition of the gun.  It does NOT disappoint!

Contact via email for fast response (it goes straight to my phone).  Buyer will have to provide a North Carolina pistol purchase permit, or a copy of his/her concealed handgun permit, and will have to sign a Bill of Sale.  Face to face sales for NC residents preferred.  I will make all attempts to meet you somewhere "in the middle" if you live far away for the right price.  Out of state residents will need to provide valid FFL.

Thanks for looking.

I have for sale a current issue 1P63 Obzor optic. This is a very unique sight for any AK platform rifle or pistol. It is solar illuminated during the daylight, and during the night it is lit by tritium inside the optic. During twilight or inside, it is illuminated by both. It also has a contrast filter to allow you to see the reticle in any light situation, including looking directly at the sun (not advised, but I'm not your mama).

This is a very durable and surprisingly lightweight "dot" sight. It will mount to any AK with a side rail and will hold zero perfectly when being taken on and off, or beat around on the rifle.

What is Lobby Day? Its a day where anyone can lobby their lawmakers for future laws they want passed, or don't want passed. It happens in Richmond at the General Assembly building. 

WHY???  For us gun owners we need to be there to lobby them for our 2nd amendment rights. Our new Governor has already said he is going to push for gun control. And remember, NYC Mayor Bloomberg gave $millions$ of his money to the Democratic campaign here in Va in November. And Bloomberg is about as anti-gun as anyone I've ever seen. He will want a return on his investment....our guns!!

SO WHAT CAN YOU DO?   Show up for Lobby Day. You don't have to give a speech or do anything uncomfortable. Mainly you just need to be seen. WE NEED NUMBERS OF PEOPLE THERE, AN OCEAN OF GUN OWNERS OUTSIDE OF THAT BUILDING. The VCDL will be there passing out GUNS SAVE LIVE stickers. Put a sticker on your shirt and be seen!!!!!! 
For more info visit these websites and learn more.

We all need to be there!!!!!

http://vcdl.org/ 
http://www.ar15.com/forums/t_8_24/543086_VCDL_Lobby_Day_20_Jan_2014___UPDATE_24_Nov_2013.html
http://www.vaguntrader.com/forums/ubbthreads.php/forum_summary
